definition: strong/powerful/better/slightly more than/vigorous/violent/best in their category, e.g. see 百強|百强[bai3 qiang2]
to force/to compel/to strive/to make an effort
classifier for a ream of paper
to order/to command/an order/warrant/writ/to cause/to make sth happen/virtuous/honorific title/season/government position (old)

sentences.english: Once again, he had forced back the Army of the Potomac.
sentences.chinese: 他再一次地強令召回了波托馬克河的部隊。

sentences.english: The Cryobiology Laboratory is opening again after the government enforced closure.
sentences.chinese: 低溫生物實驗室在被政府強令關閉後又將再度開啓。
